body:
@ctubbsii - So I've made a few comments already as I'm sure you saw but just to summarize there are 2 main things that need to be decided/agreed on so I can move forward and make changes.

1. Do we keep the output the same or update it? Obviously you are in favor of keeping things simple and not changing the output. @EdColeman was the one who initially suggested the format changes and from his recent comment he still is in favor of it for the reasons provided. We could make any format changes a follow on Issue if we wanted to do that to keep the scope of this PR smaller but as part of those changes I had to add extra logic and tracking and a new API to return the extra information to be displayed. `getEstimatedDiskUsage()` was added and returns the new object I created `TableDiskUsageResult` which supports the new format. If we don't intend to change the output then I can certainly just drop the new api/object and re-use the old API as suggested. I could go either way, mostly I would say the output should be whatever is most useful to the people who would be using the command. So really just need to make sure we are on the same page and then I can update this to do whatever.
2. As noted, old implementation is server side vs client side for the Metadata scan currently. If we just want to keep it simple and just drop the HDFS implementation for getting file sizes and go with Metadata and not change command output then what should we do about the existing Thrift server call that wouldn't be needed?

We could do something like the following.

```
